    "intro": "Interpretation presses past what the text says to what it means — tracing Moses' authorial intent in his original context (Israel poised on the plains of Moab, ca. 1406 BC) and tracing its canonical coherence forward into the New Testament. The movements below follow the chapter's pericope structure: three prohibited territories, the generational hinge, and the Sihon campaign.",
